Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Set/StrictSuperSet

Syntax Exp1 > Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 > Exp2
set[T1] set[T2] bool
Description Yields true if the vaue of Exp1 is a strict superset of the value of Exp2, and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>{1, 2, 3, 4} > {3, 2, 1};
bool: true
rascal>{1, 2, 3, 4} > {4, 3, 2, 1};
bool: false
